remembering to bring my ID so the cashier can prove I’m 18 and above when buying cigarettes.

kackers: Even as a teenager in Britian, I have demanded to prove I'm above the legal age when buying alcohol at a shop since maybe 14. 

smileysto7: But were you able to buy alcohol, let alone cigarettes?

kackers: Yes, as they ask for your age, you provide ID and that proves you're of age. It's the law in the UK. 

smileysto7: In France, to legally by cigarettes you must provide a piece of ID with a picture and be eligible for an exemption from restricting your publicity to products for adults only.

kackers: Doesn't that make it extremely easy for teenagers to get alcohol?

smileysto7: No, because the ID has your birthday on it. You have to be 16 (1 year and a month past the 15) in France.

kackers: I can't imagine most stores will bother checking your ID. But yeah, in the States they check my ID for everything. 

smileysto7: I forgot to tell you, there's a catch : in France, smoking is done by filters here, there are very little ways propositions, and they don't sell e-cigarettes.

The law is open to any cultural/behavioural changes, and it's done this way because research proves it's efficient
